tts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator#" data-google-interstitial=3D"false">top o=
f this page</a> to calculate them for your specific scenario.</p>



<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-2" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 "></span><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Kilowatts vs Kilowatt Hours: What'=
s the Difference?</h2>



<p>Kilowatts (kW) and kilowatt hours (kWh) are both units related to power,=
 energy, and electricity, but they refer to different concepts.</p><div id=
=3D"AdThrive_Content_1_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthri=
ve-content-1 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<p>A <strong>kilowatt</strong> is a measure of how much <em>power</em> is b=
eing used or produced <em>at a given moment.</em></p>



<p>A <strong>kilowatt hour</strong> is a measure of how much <em>energy</em=
> has been used or produced <em>over a period of time.</em></p>



<p>I think the most helpful analogy for understanding the difference betwee=
n kilowatts and kilowatt hours is to consider the difference between speed =
and distance. Think of kilowatts as the <em>speed</em> at which you're driv=
ing a car, while kilowatt hours is the total <em>distance</em> you've trave=
led.</p>



<p>If you drive a car at a speed of 50 mph for 1 hour, you've traveled a di=
stance of 50 miles (50 mph =C3=97 1 hr =3D 50 mi).</p>



<p>Likewise, if a device uses 2 kilowatts of power for 10 hours, it has use=
d 20 kilowatt hours of energy (2 kW =C3=97 10 hrs =3D 20 kWh).</p><div id=
=3D"AdThrive_Content_2_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthri=
ve-content-2 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-3" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 "></span><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How to Convert Kilowatts to Kilowa=
tt Hours (kW to kWh)</h2>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img fetchpriority=
=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1024" height=3D"576" data-pin-url=3D"=
https://footprinthero.com/kilowatts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator?tp_image_i=
d=3D10840" data-pin-title=3D"Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours (kW to kWh) Conver=
sion Calculator" src=3D"https://footprinthero.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/0=
8/Kilowatts-to-Kilowatt-Hours-Calculator-Image-1-1024x576.jpg" alt=3D"" cla=
ss=3D"wp-image-10840"></figure>



<p>To convert kilowatts to kilowatt hours, simply multiply kilowatts by hou=
rs.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_3_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-=
content adthrive-content-3 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></=
div>



<p><strong>Conversion formula:</strong> kilowatt hours =3D kilowatts =C3=97=
 hours</p>



<p><strong>Abbreviated formula:</strong> kWh =3D kW =C3=97 hrs</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Example</h3>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img decoding=3D"as=
ync" width=3D"1024" height=3D"768" data-pin-url=3D"https://footprinthero.co=
m/kilowatts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator?tp_image_id=3D10862" data-pin-titl=
e=3D"Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours (kW to kWh) Conversion Calculator" src=3D"=
https://footprinthero.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Kilowatts-to-Kilowatt-=
Hours-Calculator-Image-2-1024x768.jpeg" alt=3D"" class=3D"wp-image-10862"><=
/figure>



<p>Let's say your water heater uses 1.5 kilowatts and runs for around 5 hou=
rs per day.</p>



<p>Here's how you'd calculate its daily energy consumption in kilowatt hour=
s:</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">1.5 kW =C3=97 5 hrs =3D 7.5 kWh</pre>



<p>Your water heater consumes 7.5 kilowatt hours of electricity per day.</p=
>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Why Convert Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours?</h3=
>



<p>There are 2 main reasons to convert kilowatt to kilowatt hours:</p><div =
id=3D"AdThrive_Content_4_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adth=
rive-content-4 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<ol class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>To estimate how much energy a device or appliance uses</li>



<li>To estimate how much energy a power source, such as solar panel system =
or generator, produces</li>
</ol>



<h4 class=3D"wp-block-heading">1. Estimating Energy Usage of an Appliance</=
h4>



<p>Your power bill is based on how many kilowatt hours you use per month. S=
o calculating an appliance's energy usage in kilowatt hours helps you deter=
mine how much it costs to run that appliance. (I talk more about how to cal=
culate this in the next section.)</p>



<p>Alternatively, if you're building an off-grid solar or electrical system=
 (such as in a boat or RV), estimating your system's energy usage in kilowa=
tt hours will help you size your battery bank. This is called an energy aud=
it, and you can use our <a href=3D"https://footprinthero.com/solar-load-cal=
culator" data-type=3D"post" data-id=3D"11324" data-google-interstitial=3D"f=
alse">solar load (kWh) calculator</a> to help with that.</p>



<h4 class=3D"wp-block-heading">2. Estimating Energy Production of a Power S=
ource</h4>



<p>Converting kilowatts to kilowatt hours is also useful when sizing a powe=
r source, such as a generator or solar panel system.</p>



<p>Let's say you're considering putting solar panels on your roof. You get =
a quote for a 5kW solar system, and the solar installer estimates that the =
system will operate at max power output for around 5 hours a day on average=
.</p>



<p>Using these values, you could estimate the system's daily energy product=
ion by multiplying kilowatts by hours:</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_5_tab=
let" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthrive-content-5 adthrive-ad-c=
ls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">5 kW =C3=97 5 hrs =3D 25 kWh</pre>



<p>So, on an average day, you'd expect your system would generate around 25=
 kilowatt hours. (This scenario is extremely simplified and given just for =
illustrative purposes.)</p>



<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-4" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 "></span><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How to Calculate Kilowatt Hours fo=
r an Appliance</h2>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img decoding=3D"as=
ync" width=3D"1024" height=3D"768" data-pin-url=3D"https://footprinthero.co=
m/kilowatts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator?tp_image_id=3D10863" data-pin-titl=
e=3D"Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours (kW to kWh) Conversion Calculator" src=3D"=
https://footprinthero.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Kilowatts-to-Kilowatt-=
Hours-Calculator-Image-3-1024x768.jpeg" alt=3D"" class=3D"wp-image-10863"><=
/figure><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_6_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive=
-content adthrive-content-6 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"><=
/div>



<p>To estimate an appliance's energy usage in kilowatt hours, you'll need t=
he following info:</p>



<ol class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Its power consumption in watts or kilowatts</li>



<li>How many hours it runs for</li>
</ol>



<p>For instance, let's say you're trying to calculate how many kilowatt hou=
rs your dryer uses.</p>



<p>To find its power consumption, you'll need to look at its label or in th=
e product manual, or search for it online. Mine didn't have its wattage lis=
ted anywhere on the label, so I Googled the model name plus the word "watta=
ge" and learned that it uses 4.5 kilowatts.</p>



<p class=3D"has-ast-global-color-4-background-color has-background"><strong=
>Note:</strong> If your appliance's power consumption is listed in watts (W=
) rather than kilowatts, you can convert watts to kilowatts by simply divid=
ing by 1000. Say my dryer's power consumption had instead been listed as 45=
00 watts; I could've just divided 4500 =C3=B7 1000 to get 4.5 kilowatts.</p=
>



<p>Great -- I know my dryer's power draw in kilowatts.</p>



<p>Next I need to figure out how many hours it runs for. You could of cours=
e time how long it takes to dry your clothes and get exact numbers, but I'l=
l keep it simple and estimate that each dry cycle takes on average 30 minut=
es.</p>



<p>To calculate the kilowatt hours used each time you run your dryer, you'd=
 multiply its power usage in kilowatts by the runtime in hours:</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">4.5 kW =C3=97 0.5 hrs =3D 2.25 kWh</pr=
e>



<p>So, your dryer uses around <strong>2.25 kilowatt hours of electricity</s=
trong> every time you run it.</p>



<p>You can go one step further and estimate how much money it costs to run =
your dryer by multiplying its kilowatt hours by the cost of electricity in =
your area. Your cost per kilowatt hour is listed in your power bill.</p>



<p>For instance, where I live, electricity costs $0.11 per kWh. To estimate=
 how much it costs to run my dryer once, I multiply its electricity usage b=
y my cost of electricity.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_7_tablet" class=3D=
"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthrive-content-7 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"=
min-height: 250px;"></div>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">2.25 kWh =C3=97 $0.11/kWh =3D $0.2475<=
/pre>



<p>So, in this example, it would cost around <strong>$0.25</strong> every t=
ime I run my dryer.</p>



<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-5" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 "></span><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How to Convert Watts to Kilowatt H=
ours (W to kWh)</h2>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading=3D"laz=
y" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1024" height=3D"576" data-pin-url=3D"https:/=
/footprinthero.com/kilowatts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator?tp_image_id=3D745=
7" data-pin-title=3D"Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours (kW to kWh) Conversion Cal=
culator" src=3D"https://footprinthero.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Watts-=
to-Kilowatt-Hours-Calculator-Image-1-1024x576.jpg" alt=3D"" class=3D"wp-ima=
ge-7457"></figure>



<p>Some devices and appliances list their power consumption in watts (W) ra=
ther than kilowatts. 1 kilowatt is equal to 1000 watts. So, to convert watt=
s to kilowatt hours, you multiply watts by hours and then divide by 1000.</=
p>



<p><strong>Conversion formula:</strong> kilowatt hours =3D watts =C3=97 hou=
rs =C3=B7 1000</p>



<p><strong>Abbreviated formula:</strong> kWh =3D W =C3=97 hrs =C3=B7 1000</=
p>



<p><strong>Calculator:</strong> <a href=3D"https://footprinthero.com/watts-=
to-kilowatt-hours-calculator" data-type=3D"post" data-id=3D"7355" data-goog=
le-interstitial=3D"false">Watts to Kilowatt Hours Conversion Calculator</a>=
</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Example</h3>



<p>Let's say you have an LED lightbulb that consumes 10 watts.</p><div id=
=3D"AdThrive_Content_8_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthri=
ve-content-8 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading=3D"laz=
y" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1024" height=3D"768" data-pin-url=3D"https:/=
/footprinthero.com/kilowatts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator?tp_image_id=3D570=
5" data-pin-title=3D"Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours (kW to kWh) Conversion Cal=
culator" src=3D"https://footprinthero.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Watts-=
to-Watt-Hours-Calculator-Image-1-1024x768.jpg" alt=3D"" class=3D"wp-image-5=
705"><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-caption">This 60-watt equivalent LED l=
ightbulb actually consumes only 10 watts.</figcaption></figure>



<p>This bulb is in a lamp that you leave on for an average of 6 hours a day=
. How many kilowatt hours is the lamp using each month?</p>



<p>Well, first we need to calculate how many hours the bulb is on each mont=
h.</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">6 hrs =C3=97 30 days =3D 180 hrs per m=
onth</pre>



<p>So the bulb is on for 180 hours every month. Now we can calculate its mo=
nthly energy consumption in kilowatt hours.</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">10 W =C3=97 180 hrs =C3=B7 1000 =3D 1.=
8 kWh</pre>



<p>Your lamp uses 1.8 kilowatt hours of energy every month. In the grand sc=
heme of things, that's paltry compared to the energy consumption of other a=
ppliances in a typical house. AC units, water heaters, fridges, and dryers =
are usually the real energy hogs.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_9_tablet" =
class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthrive-content-9 adthrive-ad-cls" s=
tyle=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-6" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 "></span><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How to Convert Kilowatt Hours to K=
ilowatts (kWh to kW)</h2>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading=3D"laz=
y" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1024" height=3D"576" data-pin-url=3D"https:/=
/footprinthero.com/kilowatts-to-kilowatt-hours-calculator?tp_image_id=3D108=
42" data-pin-title=3D"Kilowatts to Kilowatt Hours (kW to kWh) Conversion Ca=
lculator" src=3D"https://footprinthero.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Kilow=
att-Hours-to-Kilowatts-Calculator-Image-1-1024x576.jpg" alt=3D"" class=3D"w=
p-image-10842"></figure>



<p>Need to convert the other way?</p>



<p>To convert kilowatt hours to kilowatts, divide kilowatt hours by hours.<=
/p>



<p><strong>Conversion formula:</strong> kilowatts =3D kilowatt hours =C3=B7=
 hours</p>



<p><strong>Abbreviated formula:</strong> kW =3D kWh =C3=B7 hrs</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Example</h3>



<p>Let's say your house uses on average 21 kWh per day. What is your house'=
s average power usage in kilowatts?</p>



<p>To calculate this, you'd simply divide kilowatt hours by the number of h=
ours in a day:</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-preformatted">21 kWh =C3=B7 24 hrs =3D 0.875 kW</pre=
>



<p>So, your house is using on average 0.875 kilowatts, or 875 watts.</p><di=
